{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17418440","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17418440"},"attributes":{"position":2,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T10:35:16+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T10:35:16+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261514"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261514"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1252"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17493206","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17493206"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T07:00:31+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T07:00:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1252"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261514","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1261514"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T10:35:00+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T10:36:42+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":7,"questionsAnswered":6,"marksTotal":6,"marksAttainable":6,"marksAttempted":6,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T10:35:40+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0,"questionsCorrect":0,"marksCorrect":0},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"1252","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1252"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.58,0.08,0.16,0.03,0.15]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1252"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"5606"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1252","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1252"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1252"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"5606"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"680"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1469"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3074"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7249"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"5606","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/5606"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 30-year-old man is brought to the Emergency Department short of breath and with rigors. He was unwell last week with an admission to a psychiatry ward for acute psychosis on the background of schizophrenia. Several of his medications were titrated during this admission. At that time, he was started on olanzapine.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EToday, he is confused, drowsy, and rousable only to painful stimuli. His pulse rate is 110/min, blood pressure 170/80mmHg, respiratory rate 24/min, and temperature 38.9C. His chest is clear on auscultation. His limbs are rigid on examination. A repeat blood pressure five minutes later is 120/60mmHg.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following laboratory test results would be most in keeping with his current condition?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Elevated lactate dehydrogenase","Hypokalaemia","Hypercalcaemia","Reduced creatinine","Leukopaenia"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe clinical presentation with hyperthermia, altered mental status, muscle rigidity and autonomic dysfunction in the setting of recent commencement of antipsychotic medications should raise suspicion for neuroleptic malignant syndrome (NMS).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENMS is a potentially life threatening idiosyncratic reaction to antipsychotic medications, and has been associated with practically all neuroleptics including atypical antipsychotics such as olanzapine. Although relatively uncommon, NMS should always be considered in patients with fever and altered mental status as early recognition and prompt cessation of the offending agent can significant improve morbidity and mortality. Common associated laboratory findings include \u003Cstrong\u003Eleucocytosis\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Eelevated creatinine kinase\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Eelevated lactate dehydrogenase\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn any febrile patient, organic causes of fever such as infection must be appropriately excluded.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["NMS is a potentially life threatening reaction to antipsychotic medications, and has been associated with practically all neuroleptics including atypical antipsychotics such as olanzapine.","Presentation with hyperthermia, altered mental status and muscle rigidity in the setting of recent commencement or titration of antipsychotic medications should raise suspicion for neuroleptic malignant syndrome (NMS)."],"references":["Jamshidi N, Dawson A. The hot patient: acute drug-induced hyperthermia. Australian Prescriber. 2019;42(1):24.","Kogoj A, Velikonja I. Olanzapine induced neuroleptic malignant syndrome?a case review. Human Psychopharmacology: Clinical and Experimental. 2003;18(4):301-309.","Berman B. Neuroleptic Malignant Syndrome. The Neurohospitalist. 2011;1(1):41-47."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"5606"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1252"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"5606","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/5606"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2021-06-29T00:24:39+09:30","updatedAt":"2021-06-29T00:24:39+09:30"},"rela